President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Connecticut and ordered federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts after a severe storm that occurred on October 29-30, 2011. The federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures in various counties. Stephen M. De Blasio Sr. has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.